B.Mc=new A.cs("The Sound","Fibrillations sound like 'rain on a tin roof'. PSWs sound like a 'dull thud'.")
B.LK=new A.cs("The Look","Fibrillations are brief spikes (1-5ms) with an initial positive (downward) deflection. PSWs have that same initial positive spike followed by a slow, sweeping negative return.")
B.LR=new A.cs("The Rate","Regular, rhythmic firing between 0.5-10Hz.")
B.M8=new A.cs("The Timeline","These do not appear instantly. Give them 1-3 weeks (or longer) post-injury to develop depending on the distance from the lesion to the muscle.")
