B.LG=new A.cs("Endplate Noise (MEPPs)","Monophasic negative (upward) potentials causing a continuous 'seashell' roaring sound in the background.")
B.LN=new A.cs("Endplate Spikes","Biphasic potentials caused by needle irritation. They look like fibrillations but ALWAYS have an initial negative (upward) deflection.")
B.M6=new A.cs("The Golden Rule","Endplate potentials start UP (negative). Fibrillation potentials start DOWN (positive). Never call a fib if it starts upward.")
B.M9=new A.cs("The Sound","An irregular, painful 'sputtering' sound. The patient will likely tell you that spot hurts.")
