c1=A.ce("Right S1 Radiculopathy",c3,k0,e2,A.a([A.t(!0,f0,f0,j8,f0,h3,m4,m5,f0,h4,m6,f0),A.t(!0,f0,f0,h2,f0,h3,ad1,ad2,f0,h4,r5,f0),A.t(!0,f0,f0,q5,f0,p2,ad3,f0,f0,p2,"S1",f0),A.t(!1,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,l5,l6,f0,f0,l7,f0),A.t(!1,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,m0,l6,f0,f0,m1,f0),A.t(!1,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,m2,q7,f0,f0,m1,f0),A.t(!1,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,m7,m8,f0,f0,q9,f0)],n),"Right S1 radiculopathy characterized by lower back pain radiating to the lateral foot, an absent right Achilles reflex, and weak plantarflexion. The diagnosis is confirmed by 1) Preserved SNAPs (Sural), 2) H-reflex delay, and 3) Denervation in the S1 myotome muscles (Gastroc, Gluteus Maximus) and S1 paraspinals.",c2,"s1radiculopathy",c4,ae7,ae6,!0,c1,A.a(["S1 radiculopathy classically presents with a diminished or absent Achilles reflex (S1 arc).","The H-reflex is the electrophysiological equivalent of the Achilles reflex and is a sensitive marker for S1 root dysfunction.","Normal Sural SNAP in the setting of S1 sensory loss localizes the lesion as pre-ganglionic (at the root level)."],af2),"Lower Back Pain with Foot Weakness")
ae6=A.cd(48,"8-month history of progressive numbness and weakness in right hand with neck pain",i1,"Symptoms include numbness in ring and little fingers, weakness gripping objects, and neck pain radiating down right arm. Recently developed difficulty with fine motor tasks like typing. Symptoms worse with prolonged computer use and overhead activities.","Metformin, gabapentin","Software Programmer","Cervical disc disease, Type 2 Diabetes")
